	<h2>Introduction:</h2>
	This lab exercises the ability to:
	<ul>
	    <li>Implement select JavaScript/HTML <i>event handlers</i> to enable <i>dynamic</i> Web page behavior</li>
	</ul>
	<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

	Create a Web page which incorporates the requirements in each of the following Exercises in Reed:
	<ol>
	    <li> <u>Exercise 4.9</u> </li>
	    <ul>
		<li>This will remain at the bottom of the page.
	    </ul>
	    <li> <u>Exercise 4.10</u> </li>
	    <ul>
		<li>Display the <a href="http://www.devtopics.com/101-great-computer-programming-quotes">quotation</a> when you <u>click</u> on an <u>image</u>.
	    </ul>
	    <li> <u>Exercise 4.11</u> </li>
	    <li> <u>Exercise 4.13</u> </li>
	    <ul>
		<li>Below the quotations, center an image that doubles the dimensions of the image <b><tt>ONMOUSEOVER</tt></b>, 
		    and restores the original size <b><tt>ONMOUSEOUT</tt></b>. 
	    </ul>
	    <li> <u>Exercise 4.15</u> </li>
	    <ul>
		<li>Change the color of the centered page heading (e.g. "<b><tt>Computing Quotes</tt></b>").
	    </ul>
	</ol>
	    <p>
	    When finished (after you&rsquo;ve tested and proofread each of your Web pages),<br>
	    demonstrate features of your Webpage to the instructor or graduate assistant,<br>
	    then submit your <b>three</b> sets of files to the appropriate D2L dropbox.
